OL,3,CBlue plaque unveiled in honour of man
OL,4,Cthat brought the stars to Batley
OL,6,FFor decades the Batley Variety Club
OL,7,Fwas one of the top entertainment
OL,8,Fvenues in the North of England.
OL,10,FStars such as Shirley Bassey,
OL,11,FMorecambe and Wise, Eartha Kitt and
OL,12,FLouis Armstrong performed there, along
OL,13,Fwith the Bee Gees to Tom Jones.
OL,15,FIt opened in the 1967 and was the idea
OL,16,Fof businessman James Corrigan.
OL,18,FOn Thursday (16 May), a blue plaque in
OL,19,FCorrigan's honour was unveiled on the
OL,20,Fbuilding to pay tribute to its
OL,21,Ffounder, who died in 2000.
