OL,3,CBlue plaque unveiled in honour of man
OL,4,Cthat brought the stars to Batley
OL,6,FAt its height, the club was drawing
OL,7,Fcapacity audiences of 2,500 and had a
OL,8,Fmembership of 300,000 eager to see
OL,9,Finternational stars.
OL,11,FSinger Louis Armstrong even shared his
OL,12,Fmemories of the club. Describing it
OL,13,F"living aspirin".
OL,15,F"This place, evidently everyone here
OL,16,Fknows where it is. But all I got to
OL,17,Fsay about Batley is, it's a living
OL,18,Faspirin."
